# Angular Template Syntax (Modern Control Flow)

This project uses Angular 20+. Always use the built-in control flow blocks. Never use structural directives from CommonModule.

## Conditional Rendering

Use `@if` / `@else if` / `@else` instead of `*ngIf`.

```html
<!-- BAD - structural directive -->
<div *ngIf="isOpen()">Content</div>
<div *ngIf="items().length > 0; else emptyState">Has items</div>
<ng-template #emptyState><p>No items</p></ng-template>

<!-- GOOD - built-in control flow -->
@if (isOpen()) {
  <div>Content</div>
}

@if (items().length > 0) {
  <div>Has items</div>
} @else {
  <p>No items</p>
}
```

## Loops

Use `@for` with a required `track` expression instead of `*ngFor`.

```html
<!-- BAD - structural directive -->
<div *ngFor="let item of items(); trackBy: trackById">
  {{ item.name }}
</div>

<!-- GOOD - built-in control flow with @empty -->
@for (item of items(); track item.id) {
  <div>{{ item.name }}</div>
} @empty {
  <p>No items found.</p>
}
```

## Switch Statements

Use `@switch` / `@case` / `@default` instead of `[ngSwitch]`.

```html
<!-- BAD - directive-based -->
<div [ngSwitch]="status()">
  <span *ngSwitchCase="'active'">Active</span>
  <span *ngSwitchCase="'inactive'">Inactive</span>
  <span *ngSwitchDefault>Unknown</span>
</div>

<!-- GOOD - built-in control flow -->
@switch (status()) {
  @case ('active') { <span>Active</span> }
  @case ('inactive') { <span>Inactive</span> }
  @default { <span>Unknown</span> }
}
```

## Deferred Loading

Use `@defer` for lazy-loading heavy components.

```html
@defer (on viewport) {
  <app-heavy-chart [data]="chartData()" />
} @placeholder {
  <div class="skeleton-loader"></div>
} @loading (minimum 200ms) {
  <app-spinner />
}
```

## Class & Style Bindings

Use `[class.name]` for single classes instead of importing `NgClass`. Reserve `[ngClass]` only for complex dynamic class maps.

```html
<!-- BAD - importing NgClass for a single conditional class -->
<div [ngClass]="{'dark-mode': theme() === 'dark'}">...</div>

<!-- GOOD - direct class binding -->
<div [class.dark-mode]="theme() === 'dark'">...</div>

<!-- OK - ngClass for many dynamic classes (but prefer [class.x] when possible) -->
<div [ngClass]="dynamicClassMap()">...</div>
```

## Do Not Import These From CommonModule

The built-in control flow replaces these directives entirely -- do not import them:

- `NgIf` / `*ngIf`
- `NgFor` / `*ngFor`
- `NgSwitch` / `*ngSwitch` / `*ngSwitchCase` / `*ngSwitchDefault`
- `NgClass` (for simple cases, use `[class.x]` binding instead)

If a component only used `CommonModule` for the above directives, remove the import entirely.
